column12: 2 = still an easy problem if we know some fundamental data structures and algorithms; just needs a bit more time and thinking
3 = some good idea needed in addition to 2; making it a decently hard problem
4 = more edge cases / workarounds in addition to the complexity of 3; challenging
5 = generally hard problem; need to think every step twice; code has to be optimal
* = solved by other means; not by coding in python; outlier problems
